# ETL dry-run proof (D-078 follow-up) — RoomPlan-generated IFC through the AIM ETL
#
# Command (from repo root, no DATABASE_URL — --dry-run never touches the DB):
#   python -m etl.main --file experiments/roomplan-to-ifc/converter/out/room_with_furniture.ifc --dry-run
#
# Proves the converter output is ingestible by the production ETL: it stages
# site/building/floor/space + 10 assets (4 walls, door, window, 4 furniture).
# Openings (IfcOpeningElement) are correctly excluded by the D-034 import scope
# filter ("asset, bez otvorov: 10"); all refs fall back to ifc_guid because the
# synthetic Names carry no SNIM Assembly Code — counted, not an error.
# ================================================================================

